@lsm5 You can see it in action on this PR: https://github.com/containers/podman/actions/runs/19876571900/job/56965285016?pr=27663

So it runs Zizmor and finds the unresolved issues with the use of `pull_request_target` triggers (you can see it in the action logs in the "run zizmor" step), but this does *not* cause the workflow itself to fail—instead, the results are uploaded in SARIF format to integrate with GitHub Advanced Security, which (for code on the default branch) will display them in the "code scanning" section of the security tab once the PR is merged.

Additionally, these results get displayed as code annotations on PRs, but that only happens on PRs that modify the files that would receive annotations, which is why you don't see any such annotations on this PR: Zizmor doesn't have code scanning results for any files this PR touches.

@HastD thanks, LGTM

The testing-farm tests can be ignored for now.

@containers/podman-maintainers PTAL.
